**Loan Against Property (LAP)** is a secured loan where you mortgage your residential, commercial, or industrial property to borrow funds. LAP interest rates (9–15% p.a.) are lower than personal loans because the loan is secured by real estate. You can use LAP proceeds for any purpose — business expansion, medical expenses, education, or debt consolidation.
